# taste 

Clojure-based service that runs in Jetty and stores user taste profiles in MongoDB.

## Usage

1. Download lein:
    sudo curl https://raw.github.com/technomancy/leiningen/preview/bin/lein -o /usr/bin/lein && sudo chmod +x /usr/bin/lein

2. Ensure that http_proxy is set:
    export http_proxy=172.16.44.133:8080

3. Run this command to start the app with Jetty:
    lein embongo ring server
    or
    lein ring server (if you already have mongo running)

4. Inspect src/core.clj for urls to hit, e.g.:
    curl "http://localhost:3000/1.x/status"

5. Run this command to run the tests:
    lein embongo test :all
